checkrule_set.description:
The POM Code Convention is the Maven project's internal recommendation for POM element ordering. It calls for listing modifiers in the following
order:

  1.  &lt;modelVersion/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;parent/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;groupId/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;artifactId/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;version/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;packaging/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;name/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;description/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;url/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;inceptionYear/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;organization/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;licenses/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;developers/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;contributors/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;mailingLists/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;prerequisites/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;modules/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;scm/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;issueManagement/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;ciManagement/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;distributionManagement/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;properties/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;dependencyManagement/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;dependencies/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;repositories/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;pluginRepositories/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;build/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;reporting/&gt; 
  1.  &lt;profiles/&gt; 

Not following this convention has no technical impact, but will reduce the pom's readability because most developers are used to the standard
order.

## See

  -  [POM Code Convention](https://maven.apache.org/developers/conventions/code.html#POM_Code_Convention)
